report_title: 2023 San Francisco Supervisor District 10 Crime Statistics
subtitle: Supervisor: Shamann Walton
summary: In Supervisor District 10 during 2023, there were 443 crimes and 191 dispositions. 338 cases were presented from the 443 crimes, and 163 of those cases were filed by the San Francisco District Attorney's Offfice. 260 cases were filed as felonies, and 78 cases were filed as misdemeanors. Multiple crimes can be associated with a single court case. Out of 154 felony dispositions: 57 were convictions, 39 were post-filing diversions, 30 were other D.A. office actions, 27 were dismissed post-filing, and 1 were acquittals. Out of 37 misdemeanor dispositions: 7 were convictions, 15 were post-filing diversions, 6 were other D.A. office actions, 9 were dismissed post-filing, and 0 were acquittals. The data visualized in this report is current as of June 30, 2023.
